        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 6 at 6:35PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 635 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles southwest of Limon, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Limon, Hugo, Genoa and Cedar Point.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Prepare for sudden gusty winds. Secure loose objects and move to a
safe shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
